Additionally, the paper involves some concepts from discrete mathematics, such as matroid parity, which could classify it under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves some concepts from graph theory and game theory, such as weighted matching and abelian groups, which could classify it under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper involves some concepts from complexity theory, such as pseudopolynomial-time algorithms and strongly polynomial-time algorithms, which could classify it under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
